==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Zhou Zhongbing (2024): {{Han compound|隹|小|ls=psc|t1=bird|c1=s|c2=p}}<ref>[https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/n1OMFi_DTBkTscfgdDtJKg 周忠兵：釋甲骨文中的“焦”]</ref> — original form of {{och-l|鷦|a kind of bird}}. During the Warring States period, {{och-l|*小}} corrupted into {{och-l|*火}}, after which it was borrowed to represent {{och-l|焦|to scorch}}.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=𤊙,𩵰,㸈,𤓪,𤓬}}
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*tsjow||to boil; to burn; to cook; to bake}}. Cognate with {{cog|bo|འཚོད||to cook}}, {{cog|my|ဆူ||to boil}}. Compare also the following Sinitic words (STEDT):
* {{och-l|燋|to roast, burn, scorch; torch}}
* {{och-l|樵|to gather firewood; firewood; burn fuel}}
* {{och-l|爝|torch}}
* {{och-l|竈|stove, kitchen}}

